# Phase 32: Multi-Chain Production Payments

Goal: Harden the prototype into a production-grade, non-custodial, multi-chain payment system with real wallet addresses and on-chain smart contracts for 75/25 splitting. Ensure all UI buttons are functional.

---

## ⚠️ Wallet Security Model: NOT Hardcoded

> [!CAUTION]
> **NEVER hardcode production wallet addresses in frontend source code.** This approach is a major security risk because:
> - The entire source code is public once deployed (Next.js client bundles are readable)
> - Attackers can scan open-source repos for addresses and target them
> - You cannot update hardcoded values without a full redeploy (which is a huge operational risk)

### Recommended Approach: Environment Variables + Admin API
- **Production Wallets** → Stored as `NEXT_PUBLIC_PLATFORM_WALLET_*` environment variables in Vercel, NOT in source code
- **Updatability** → A restricted admin API (`/api/admin/update-wallets`) allows updating wallets via Supabase, with a 24h timelock confirmation to prevent a single-point compromise
- **Smart Contracts** → Contracts use an `owner()` pattern and `transferOwnership()`, requiring a 2-of-3 multisig to change the payout address

---

## Platform Wallet Configuration (Production)

All addresses below will be configured as environment variables in Vercel **and the [.env.local](file:///C:/GOLive/.env.local)** file. They will NOT appear in any client-side [.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/next-env.d.ts) file directly.

| Network | Address |
|---|---|
| **Solana** | `DDztsJc2RmC2m2DvKFoB3ActexVkdzHZqYdMd3UXY6ft` |
| **Base** | `0x5b9C3D6e92F4e6A7fD03cBC1f60da3De002BC1a8` |
| **Bitcoin** | `bc1qs0jsf7lfqgp7mg3c32cf67ahzx8r9xu2hv7gnl` (Display only, no direct smart contract) |
| **Monad (Mainnet)** | `0x5b9C3D6e92F4e6A7fD03cBC1f60da3De002BC1a8` (same as Base, EVM compatible) |

