## Proposed Changes

---

### 1. Environment & Security Layer

#### [MODIFY] [.env.local](file:///C:/GOLive/.env.local)
- Add `NEXT_PUBLIC_PLATFORM_WALLET_EVM`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_PLATFORM_WALLET_SOLANA`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_PLATFORM_WALLET_BTC`
- These are read at build time and injected into the client bundle, but the source is not committed to GitHub

#### [MODIFY] [constants.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/lib/constants.ts)
- Remove all hardcoded placeholder addresses
- Pull platform wallets from `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_*` with a safe fallback to throw an error if not set

---

### 2. Smart Contracts

#### [NEW] `contracts/vibestream-splitter/` — Base & Monad (Solidity)
A lightweight, non-upgradeable Splitter contract deployed on Base Sepolia (test) and Base Mainnet. Key properties:
- Accepts ETH or USDC
- Atomically splits 75% → creator, 25% → platform in a single transaction
- `owner` is the platform multisig wallet
- `updateFee()` requires `owner`, preventing unauthorized changes

#### [NEW] `contracts/anchor/vibestream-splitter/` — Solana (Rust/Anchor)
A Solana program that accepts SOL or USDC (SPL) and atomically distributes via CPI.
- Single transaction with multiple transfer instructions (already atomic by design)
- Program authority = platform wallet (`DDzts...`)

---

### 3. Frontend Updates

#### [MODIFY] [TipButton.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/TipButton.tsx)
- Use the deployed contract address for Base instead of sequential transfers
- Add Bitcoin display-only option (shows QR code + address for manual payment)
- Fix all button accessibility (add `aria-label`, `title`)
- Add wallet detection UX: Show "Install MetaMask" if no wallet found
- Fix amount presets for Native vs USDC (ETH/SOL have very different values vs USDC $1/$5/$20)

#### [MODIFY] [constants.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/lib/constants.ts)
- Set real wallet addresses from env vars

